  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Indication for the implantation of a defibrillator with cardiac resynchronisation
             therapy

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Cardiac surgery, acute coronary syndrome / myocardial infarction, percutaneous
             coronary intervention within the past 4 weeks

          -  Indication for coronary artery revascularisation

          -  Atrial fibrillation with insufficient rate control

          -  ASA (American Society of Anesthesiologists) class V or cardiogenic shock

          -  age &lt;18 years, pregnancy, tutelage

          -  inability to understand the patient consent for or study refusal

          -  anticipated insufficient echocardiographic image quality
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
